{
  "texts": [
    "Permutation Permuted SequenceCanonical Ordering This task is perhaps easier than our motivating examples, as the model is given both a description of the permutation to be \"undone\" as well as the permuted sequence.",
    "Nonetheless, we show that a simplified transformer model cannot learn to complete this task.",
    "[ 2 0 1] [ ♣ ♡ ♠] [ ♡ ♠ ♣] apply inverse [ 1 2 0] [ ♠ ♣ ♡] [ ♡ ♠ ♣] apply inverseContributions.",
    "In Section 2.1, we derive an impossibility result for inverse permutation learning with a decoder-only, attention-only transformer architecture.",
    "The intuition underpinning this result is straightforward: all permutations (except the trivial identity permutation) require shifting at least one element from a later position in the sequence to an earlier position in the sequence."
  ]
}